projects.description:
In the Netherlands and Belgium Travelbags is a major player in the travel luggage and bag industry. In the recent years Travelbags has grown enormously as a company. This growth is partly due to the disappearance of some major players in the market such as V&D. In this competitive market Travelbags has been able to continue their growth in a stable manner, and now wants to enter a new foreign market outside of the Netherlands and Belgium.

This project determines which foreign market offers the most options for Travelbags at this moment and in the future, given the current trends and developments. 

Responsibilities: 
• Act as a point of contact for everyone in the team, the client and other stakeholders for all questions concerning the agile way of working and scrum methodology;
• Applying scrum within the project organization (sprint planning, daily stand-ups, retrospectives, etc.);
• Organizing and facilitating meetings between Travelbags and the project team;
• Identifying and escalating of work and managing dependencies;
• Continuously improvement of the project team collaboration by collecting feedback and facilitating retrospectives.

