JICTO a young, small-scale and dynamic up-and-coming IT company, solving IT related issues in this ever expanding world of computers and electronics.

Responsibilities:
• Representing the business based upon the agile philosophy;
• Training and coaching of 2 technical support employees in self-organization;
• Developing business plan / project plans and (financial) reports;
• Responsible for purchasing hardware, software and licenses;
• Implementation of PM & CRM solution "Freelance Cockpit";
• Implementation of CRM-VoIP integration "Telzio";
• Facilitating external knowledge sessions and workshops.

As market leader in the Dutch insurance market, Achmea wants to stay ahead of innovation and become the number one digital insurer of the future.  
Achmea sees DevOps as the logical next step in their digital evolution. The introduction of DevOps delivers a significant Increase in productivity of business and IT teams. Save costs on maintenance and upgrades, and eliminate unnecessary capital expenditure.

Responsibilities:
• Initiating and applying Lean Value Stream Mapping techniques to shorten lead times, improve productivity and reduce costs;
• Supporting the transition team with the implementation of SAFe (Scaled Agile Framework) Roadmap;
• Conducting internal research that covers the (cultural) change that is needed to make Continuous Integration, Delivery and Deployment a success;
• Providing general support to the transition team, consisted of Agile Coaches, Lean Experts, and Product Owners & Scrum Masters.

Within ENGIE B2C, the New Services department is responsible for the development and introduction of new products and services, in order to remain relevant as an energy supplier in the future.

Responsibilities:
• Responsible for the development of a system, that gives insight in how many Guarantees of Origin (GvO’s) per solar producer (both B2C and B2B) have been credited to the ENGIE account;
• Responsible for the IT issue log and communication towards developers in regards to the online ENGIE energy saving tool that could be used by customers;
• Structuring / automating work so it can be integrated within the existing organization;  
• Collaborating with (and providing administrative support to) the New Services Product Managers;
• Relation management  with various stakeholders within the organization;
• Conducting research in the field of consumer energy saving.

Xerox Business Process Outsourcing (Conduent) specializes in process outsourcing, customer service, transportation solutions, healthcare and digital payments at companies as well.

Responsibilities:
• Providing technical support to customers that are using digital television, internet and telephony from Telfort;
• Writing and managing work instructions, teaching materials and documentation;
• Relationship management; first point of contact by escalations that involve customers, mechanics, experts and other departments;
• Administrating data in various systems such as Trinicom CRM and Siebel; 
• Complying with both quantitative and qualitative pressure. Based on NPS, retention and sales percentage, handling time and QM (call quality);
